nsd 4.x for Debian
==================

  Beware that using nsd commands have often to be performed as user
‘nsd’ and not ‘root’, so that the files it touches or create have the
correct permissions.

  The Debian /etc/init.d/nsd script hence contains wrappers around nsdc
performing the tasks under the proper user, avoiding the need to bother
with switching users.

 -- Ondřej Surý <ondrej@debian.org>, Sun,  6 Oct 2013 00:12:52 +0200
